<h1>Cranberry-Orange Relish</h1>
<p>Keith gave me this recipe on Dec. 2015. It is good and easy and also <b>very</b> orangey!
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1/2 cup water</li>
<li>1/2 cup orange juice</li>
<li>1 cup granulated sugar</li>
<li>1 lb whole cranberries</li>
<li>2 tablespoons grated orange rind</li>
<li>1 tablespoon Grand Marnier</li>
</ul>

<h2>Instructions</h2>

<p>In a 3-4 quart saucepan, stir the water, orange juice and sugar together until the sugar is thoroughly dissolved. add the cranberries, bring to boil, cook for 3-5 minutes, stirring occasionally until the skins of the berries begin to pop and berries are tender but not mushy. Do not overcook them.</p>

<p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir in orange rind and Grand Marnier. transfer mixture to a serving bowl, cool, and chill for at least an hour or two before serving.</p>

<p>Makes 1 quart.</p>
